Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

Dr. Li Wenliang left us.

There are many things in front of us that are painful, but do not be pessimistic. This is a time to fight with greater resolve, to move on, to console those who have lost their lives, and to provide security for those who continue to fight. To this end, the three life media, one-way space, Beijing Lianyi Charity Foundation co-sponsored art donation and auction activities, the proceeds used to support Hubei first-line medical staff.

"Life is priceless, art is powerful. "
A Pro Bono letter to friends
_

Dear artist and reader,

It was a snowy winter, destined to be unusual. Before I make a formal offer to you, let me tell you a little bit about our experience these days.

January 25 is the first day of the Lunar New Year. In the morning, we set up the "three-joint Animal Materials Coordination Group" to help hospitals in the epidemic area of Wuhan find and coordinate various medical materials. In addition to continuing to send in front-line reports, we want to do something practical.

Over the next 10 days, we helped 51 hospitals in 24 cities across the country, matching donations for supplies that were in short supply. Including more than 50,000 surgical masks of various types, more than 15,000 N95 masks, nearly 20,000 ordinary protective masks, 139 protective clothing, and 5,519 pairs of goggles for medical use, all kinds of large quantities of disinfectant, hydrogen peroxide, surgical gloves, disposable medical caps and other materials.

Among the many donors, there are two stories to keep in mind.

A bakery in Wuhan came to US and wanted to donate 200 loaves of bread. We helped him find a hospital, and he said I had 1,200 dough to donate, so I had 1,400 bread. A reader from Shanxi, who was working in Shanghai, had gone home and remembered that there was still a box of masks in his house, and that he had used one and nine. She asked a friend to find it and donated it through us. That's the only nine N95 masks we found in two days.

It's a drop in the bucket, but every ordinary person is trying to make a difference. Not to mention the health care workers who are already Remember the Titans, holding down the line. They use their bodies and courage to save every life. They're real heroes.

In the face of disease, art can not directly save lives, but it has its own power. Art allows us to hold good thoughts in difficult situations, to soothe the soul in pain, and to regain courage and hope after a storm. As Albert Camus says in the novel the plague, "As long as there is a trace of warmth, despair does not eat away at the heart. "

So right now, we also need the power of art, not only to provide substantial assistance, but also to lift the spirit, comfort people, enlightenment. For those doctors, nurses, for those who volunteer, for those who are struggling, for those who are suffering, for all of us.

Therefore, "Sanlian life weekly" and one-way space, Beijing Lianyi Charity Foundation co-sponsored "priceless life, powerful art" public welfare action. The Beijing One Way Street Foundation is particularly supportive of the campaign, and ICOUNCIL is hosting the online exhibition and auction online. Dai Ze, a famous contemporary artist, and Chen Lusheng, the former deputy director of the National Museum of China, are the special advisers to the public welfare action of art.

We cordially invite you to join us as co-sponsors of this initiative, to donate your work to the auction, to publish your ideas, and to contribute your efforts.

You can participate in this pro Bono initiative in the following ways:
Taking "the concern of all living beings under the great epidemic" as the artistic theme: No Matter Recording, sympathizing, warning or reflecting, the angle is not limited;

Contribute existing works or collections, whether calligraphy, painting, Sculpture, or manuscript, in whatever form you deem relevant;

The material and size of the work are not limited.

We also call on the vast number of cultural and artistic colleagues to act together, with love charity sales, original works of art and other rich forms of participation.

Works and collections donated by artists will be auctioned online through Quanshi. The proceeds from the auction will be used through the Beijing Lianyi Charitable Foundation to fund the care and Care Package Project for medical staff on the Wuhan "war epidemic" front, to provide personal materials for medical staff on the front line and improve their living conditions, improve job satisfaction.

In 2018, the charity Luen Yick Foundation began supporting needy children and families in Wuhan Union Hospital. After the outbreak, on January 24, Beijing Lianyi Foundation immediately set up an emergency response working group to continue to pay attention to the medical staff who rushed to support the epidemic areas. They are also in urgent need of care and care during the intensive rescue work. LIANYI team to overcome procurement difficulties, transport difficulties, first rush to transport the first batch of 1000"Lianyi care package" arrived on the front line. Subsequently, 1,220,000 medical gloves, 1,500 kilograms of disinfection tablets, nearly 10,000 protective clothing and other emergency supplies to the epidemic area hospitals and communities.
Slide to the left, photo of charity foundation supporting the epidemic area
The donation will be used to purchase the second batch of Luen Yick medical care package materials.

At that time, the specific recipients, the number, the arrival of the situation, we will be open and transparent in a timely manner, to ensure that your good will be effectively transmitted.

The timetable of this pro Bono action

First all works online exhibition and Public Auction: February 14,15;
CONTRIBUTIONS AND FOLLOW-UP: launched on 19 February and kept open and public simultaneously;
Media Display Time: from the date of receiving the information about the work.

Display Platform

Sanlian life weekly Wechat, Weibo, Kuang Shi online APP, one-way Street Bookstore Wechat, one-way Street Library Weibo.

Online auction platform

Quanshi online APP, ICOUNCIL Quanshi online wechat applet.

Information submission requirements for works

1. High definition artwork, no less than 1 MB per image.
2. Basic Information of the work, description, introduction of the main idea and introduction of the author.
If possible, we would also like you to record a Vlog of your presentation
You can sign up by clicking on the activity poster or send the above information to Info@icouncil. Com.cn  , xingyu@lifeweek. COM.CN

Selection and mailing

We will screen the entries and select the works that meet the objectives of the event and have considerable value. The staff will contact the artists directly to confirm the entries and agree on mailing.

A Pro Bono letter to friends

Dear artist and reader,

It was a snowy winter, destined to be unusual. Before I make a formal offer to you, let me tell you a little bit about our experience these days.

January 25 is the first day of the Lunar New Year. In the morning, we set up the "three-joint Animal Materials Coordination Group" to help hospitals in the epidemic area of Wuhan find and coordinate various medical materials. In addition to continuing to send in front-line reports, we want to do something practical.

Over the next 10 days, we helped 51 hospitals in 24 cities across the country, matching donations for supplies that were in short supply. Including more than 50,000 surgical masks of various types, more than 15,000 N95 masks, nearly 20,000 ordinary protective masks, 139 protective clothing, and 5,519 pairs of goggles for medical use, all kinds of large quantities of disinfectant, hydrogen peroxide, surgical gloves, disposable medical caps and other materials.

Among the many donors, there are two stories to keep in mind.

A bakery in Wuhan came to US and wanted to donate 200 loaves of bread. We helped him find a hospital, and he said I had 1,200 dough to donate, so I had 1,400 bread. A reader from Shanxi, who was working in Shanghai, had gone home and remembered that there was still a box of masks in his house, and that he had used one and nine. She asked a friend to find it and donated it through us. That's the only nine N95 masks we found in two days.

It's a drop in the bucket, but every ordinary person is trying to make a difference. Not to mention the health care workers who are already Remember the Titans, holding down the line. They use their bodies and courage to save every life. They're real heroes.

In the face of disease, art can not directly save lives, but it has its own power. Art allows us to hold good thoughts in difficult situations, to soothe the soul in pain, and to regain courage and hope after a storm. As Albert Camus says in the novel the plague, "As long as there is a trace of warmth, despair does not eat away at the heart. "

So right now, we also need the power of art, not only to provide substantial assistance, but also to lift the spirit, comfort people, enlightenment. For those doctors, nurses, for those who volunteer, for those who are struggling, for those who are suffering, for all of us.

Therefore, "Sanlian life weekly" and one-way space, Beijing Lianyi Charity Foundation co-sponsored "priceless life, powerful art" public welfare action. The Beijing One Way Street Foundation is particularly supportive of the campaign, and ICOUNCIL is hosting the online exhibition and auction online. Dai Ze, a famous contemporary artist, and Chen Lusheng, the former deputy director of the National Museum of China, are the special advisers to the public welfare action of art.

It was a snowy winter, destined to be unusual. Before I make a formal offer to you, let me tell you a little bit about our experience these days.

January 25 is the first day of the Lunar New Year. In the morning, we set up the "three-joint Animal Materials Coordination Group" to help hospitals in the epidemic area of Wuhan find and coordinate various medical materials. In addition to continuing to send in front-line reports, we want to do something practical.

Over the next 10 days, we helped 51 hospitals in 24 cities across the country, matching donations for supplies that were in short supply. Including more than 50,000 surgical masks of various types, more than 15,000 N95 masks, nearly 20,000 ordinary protective masks, 139 protective clothing, and 5,519 pairs of goggles for medical use, all kinds of large quantities of disinfectant, hydrogen peroxide, surgical gloves, disposable medical caps and other materials.

Among the many donors, there are two stories to keep in mind.

A bakery in Wuhan came to US and wanted to donate 200 loaves of bread. We helped him find a hospital, and he said I had 1,200 dough to donate, so I had 1,400 bread. A reader from Shanxi, who was working in Shanghai, had gone home and remembered that there was still a box of masks in his house, and that he had used one and nine. She asked a friend to find it and donated it through us. That's the only nine N95 masks we found in two days.

It's a drop in the bucket, but every ordinary person is trying to make a difference. Not to mention the health care workers who are already Remember the Titans, holding down the line. They use their bodies and courage to save every life. They're real heroes.

In the face of disease, art can not directly save lives, but it has its own power. Art allows us to hold good thoughts in difficult situations, to soothe the soul in pain, and to regain courage and hope after a storm. In 2018, the charity Luen Yick Foundation began supporting needy children and families in Wuhan Union Hospital. After the outbreak, on January 24, Beijing Lianyi Foundation immediately set up an emergency response working group to continue to pay attention to the medical staff who rushed to support the epidemic areas. They are also in urgent need of care and care during the intensive rescue work. LIANYI team to overcome procurement difficulties, transport difficulties, first rush to transport the first batch of 1000"Lianyi care package" arrived on the front line. Subsequently, 1,220,000 medical gloves, 1,500 kilograms of disinfection tablets, nearly 10,000 protective clothing and other emergency supplies to the epidemic area hospitals and communities.
